pl.edu.icm.cermine.parsing.model

Interface ParsableString<T extends Token<?>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the tokens
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DocumentAffiliation

    public interface ParsableString<T extends Token<?>>
    Representation of a parsable string. Such a string may be tokenized i.e. split into smaller parts (for example words). Each token may have a label corresponding to the type of its text content. The parsing process consists of tokenization followed by token classification.
    Author:
    Bartosz Tarnawski
